.TH "wait_for_completion_interruptible_timeout" 9 "wait_for_completion_interruptible_timeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wait_for_completion_interruptible_timeout \- - waits for completion (w/(to,intr))
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" wait_for_completion_interruptible_timeout
.BI "(struct completion *x "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "x" 12
holds the state of this particular completion
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout value in jiffies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This waits for either a completion of a specific task to be signaled or for a
specified timeout to expire. It is interruptible. The timeout is in jiffies.
.SH "RETURN"
-ERESTARTSYS if interrupted, 0 if timed out, positive (at least 1,
or number of jiffies left till timeout) if completed.
